She's like the new O'Malley.

91
00:04:46,603 --> 00:04:48,698
- Izzie's nothing
like O'Malley.
- Hello...

92
00:04:48,722 --> 00:04:52,073
OK, O'Malley,
you're in the clinic,

93
00:04:52,175 --> 00:04:54,921
Grey and Yang, with me.
Karev, you're in the pit with Hunt.

94
00:04:54,945 --> 00:04:56,728
Dr. Bailey, I'm on trauma today.

95
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:59,175
Save it, Yang. Hunt wants Karev.

96
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:00,682
Oh! Sir, there you are.

97
00:05:00,801 --> 00:05:03,451
Shepherd planning to
grace us with his presence?

98
00:05:03,553 --> 00:05:05,420
Yes, he's fine.

99
00:05:07,124 --> 00:05:09,591
Sir! I've been trying to
page you all morning.

100
00:05:09,693 --> 00:05:13,411
- I could use help on a case.
- No peds today?

101
00:05:13,514 --> 00:05:14,596
Uh, no.

102
00:05:14,698 --> 00:05:18,933
- Must be slumming.
- Excuse me? Sir...

103
00:05:19,970 --> 00:05:21,403
Tricia Shelley, 31,

104
00:05:21,505 --> 00:05:24,439
Megan Shelley, 27,
Michael Shelley, 23.

105
00:05:24,541 --> 00:05:28,343
Genetic testing revealed
they all carry the CDH1 gene

106
00:05:28,445 --> 00:05:30,561
for hereditary
diffuse gastric cancer.

107
00:05:30,663 --> 00:05:32,197
Which means what, Dr. Grey?

108
00:05:32,299 --> 00:05:34,977
Which means they all have a 3-in-4
chance of developing the cancer.

109
00:05:35,001 --> 00:05:38,336
Dr. Bailey's taken tumors out of
everyone on our mother's side.

110
00:05:38,438 --> 00:05:42,073
Unfortunately, it's a highly aggressive
cancer, the tumors grow quickly,

111
00:05:42,175 --> 00:05:45,677
- by the time I get in...
- Our family's tree's
down to a branch.

112
00:05:45,779 --> 00:05:49,164
How is... Uncle Bud doing?

113
00:05:49,266 --> 00:05:50,465
Dead.

114
00:05:51,468 --> 00:05:53,552
- And Aunt Helen?
- Dead.

115
00:05:53,654 --> 00:05:56,014
- What about
the Minnesota cousin?
- Not dead!

116
00:05:56,106 --> 00:06:00,108
- She's 90 pounds
and in hospice, Meg.
- Still. Not dead yet.

117
00:06:00,210 --> 00:06:04,345
So, uh, you've decided you're
ready to take the next step.

118
00:06:04,447 --> 00:06:07,131
We've made a pact,
we're all in this together.

119
00:06:07,233 --> 00:06:10,018
Cut our stomachs
out, Dr. Bailey.

120
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:19,144
Beth Dearborn, 17-year-old
with a history of seizures,

121
00:06:19,246 --> 00:06:22,980
had a grand mal during band
performance, started seizing on arrival.

122
00:06:23,083 --> 00:06:24,833
Push two of lorazepam.

123
00:06:24,935 --> 00:06:27,118
She's in v-fib! Charge
the paddles to 200.

124
00:06:27,220 --> 00:06:31,556
The v-fib could be from the seizure.
If she's not in v-fib, she'll flatline.

125
00:06:31,658 --> 00:06:34,492
- You got a pulse?
- I don't think so. It's hard to tell.

126
00:06:34,594 --> 00:06:36,795
- Lorazepam's not working.
- What do we do?

127
00:06:36,897 --> 00:06:40,131
We shock her and save
her or shock her and kill her.

128
00:06:43,136 --> 00:06:45,887
What the hell. Clear!

129
00:06:53,146 --> 00:06:54,395
Clear!

130
00:07:04,173 --> 00:07:06,190
- Sinus tach.
- Good call, Dr. Hunt.

131
00:07:06,292 --> 00:07:07,975
The odds are 50-50 shot.

132
00:07:09,679 --> 00:07:12,814
Oh, no... it happened again?

133
00:07:12,916 --> 00:07:15,833
I'm Dr. Robbins, the pediatric
surgeon on call, this is Dr. Hunt.

134
00:07:15,935 --> 00:07:19,754
You got beat up while marching,
I'm going to check for internal injuries.

135
00:07:19,857 --> 00:07:22,990
I seized during the
performance? But I took my meds...

136
00:07:23,093 --> 00:07:25,159
Relax, it's not like you
crapped your pants.

137
00:07:25,262 --> 00:07:29,164
It is like I crapped my pants. I had
a seizure in front of the entire band.

138
00:07:29,265 --> 00:07:33,818
It is exactly like I crapped my
pants. They're going to kill me.

139
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:36,187
- Who?
- Seizure patrol.

140
00:07:39,475 --> 00:07:43,294
- You're the seizure patrol?
- I'm first clarinet,
he's drum major.

141
00:07:43,396 --> 00:07:45,046
Whenever Beth has a seizure,

142
00:07:45,148 --> 00:07:49,100
we drop our instruments, roll her on her
side so she doesn't choke on her tongue.

143
00:07:49,202 --> 00:07:52,465
We were in the Northwest Regional
Parade. We were favored to win.

144
00:07:52,489 --> 00:07:55,423
Yeah, until Beth took down
the snare drum, woodwinds...

145
00:07:55,542 --> 00:07:58,242
the tubas tried to avoid
her but she was in formation.

146
00:07:58,344 --> 00:08:00,879
Yeah. Why don't you
go call her parents?

147
00:08:02,865 --> 00:08:06,234
I'm gonna run some tests, but
she's coded once, so watch her,

148
00:08:06,336 --> 00:08:09,521
- standby with a crash cart.
- You want me to baby-sit?

149
00:08:09,623 --> 00:08:12,807
- That's an intern job.
- I don't see
any interns around.

150
00:08:15,112 --> 00:08:17,162
Dr. Grey?

151
00:08:17,264 --> 00:08:20,565
Patient X, a previously
healthy 29-year-old female

152
00:08:20,667 --> 00:08:23,801
presented with stable vital
signs, a normal physical exam,

153
00:08:23,904 --> 00:08:28,356
with symptoms of right upper quadrant
pain, nausea, and hallucinations.

154
00:08:28,458 --> 00:08:31,108
Head CT, chest X-ray,
CBC were normal,

155
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:33,378
but chemistries revealed
an elevated LDH.

156
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:38,416
You are this girl's doctor, she comes to
you, scared, doesn't know what's wrong,

157
00:08:38,519 --> 00:08:41,152
you have to diagnose
her. What do you do next?

158
00:08:41,254 --> 00:08:43,950
- What test do you run?
- A retic count
or peripheral smear?

159
00:08:43,974 --> 00:08:46,774
You'd be wasting your time.
The CBC was normal, remember?

160
00:08:46,876 --> 00:08:49,794
You said there was abdominal
pain, what about an upper GI?

161
00:08:49,896 --> 00:08:51,162
Good.

162
00:08:51,264 --> 00:08:54,999
That is exactly what
Patient X's doctor did next.

163
00:08:55,802 --> 00:08:58,235
What does this tell us?

164
00:09:00,056 --> 00:09:02,857
- What is this?
- Side effects
and complications

165
00:09:02,959 --> 00:09:06,828
from prophylactic gastrectomy, so
post-op you know what to expect.

166
00:09:06,930 --> 00:09:10,281
Malnourishment, weakness,
fatigue... dumping syndrome?

167
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:13,268
- That doesn't sound good.
- Possible anal leakage?!

168
00:09:13,370 --> 00:09:16,254
A gastrectomy isn't like
getting your appendix out.

169
00:09:16,356 --> 00:09:20,342
We're changing the way your digestive
system works, a serious adjustment.

170
00:09:20,444 --> 00:09:23,528
I'm president of my frat, have
a girlfriend, go snowboarding!

171
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:27,331
How am I supposed to do that when
I'm a weak old man with anal leakage!?

172
00:09:27,433 --> 00:09:29,393
You know how
important this is to Trish.

173
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:31,603
Trish has run our lives
since we were kids,

174
00:09:31,705 --> 00:09:35,306
she decides where we go to dinner,
vacation, where we do Thanksgiving...

175
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:38,476
I'm 23. If I don't want to butcher
myself, she can't make me.

176
00:09:38,578 --> 00:09:42,680
So you'd rather die like Mom?
Or Grandpa? Or Uncle Bud?

177
00:09:42,782 --> 00:09:45,417
It's not quick, Mike. It's
a slow, painful way to go.

178
00:09:45,519 --> 00:09:48,136
There's a 1-in-4 shot
we don't get it, right?

179
00:09:49,338 --> 00:09:51,200
- That's something!
- Don't be stupid.

180
00:09:51,224 --> 00:09:52,751
You are doing
this, we discussed...

181
00:09:52,775 --> 00:09:56,077
You're not in charge
of me anymore!

182
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,598
Meg?

183
00:10:01,167 --> 00:10:04,302
I didn't realize it
was such a big deal.

184
00:10:04,404 --> 00:10:09,090
I just... I need a little
time to think about it, OK?

185
00:10:12,396 --> 00:10:16,531
No, Callahan on the
bypass, Levin on the appy.

186
00:10:16,633 --> 00:10:19,267
Damn craniotomy. Where
the hell is Shepherd?!

187
00:10:19,369 --> 00:10:22,087
You can't rely on Shepherd.
Is there anything I can do?

188
00:10:22,189 --> 00:10:26,274
My neurosurgeon has been missing
for days, I have no head of cardio,

189
00:10:26,376 --> 00:10:28,843
general surgeons quitting
on me left and right,

190
00:10:28,945 --> 00:10:31,545
surgeries piling up like
dead fish and no surgeons!

191
00:10:31,647 --> 00:10:33,330
Now would be a
bad time to tell you

192
00:10:33,432 --> 00:10:37,268
my hand's still out of
commission and I can't operate.

193
00:10:38,905 --> 00:10:41,422
Leave me on the board,
chief. I won't let you down.

194
00:10:41,524 --> 00:10:43,324
I could do that craniotomy.

195
00:10:47,263 --> 00:10:48,896
Um...

196
00:10:48,998 --> 00:10:51,349
Put Dr. Nelson
on the craniotomy.

197
00:10:52,619 --> 00:10:56,437
- Appreciate it, John.
- It... It's Jim.

198
00:10:56,539 --> 00:10:58,940
You must be new.
Welcome to Seattle Grace.

199
00:10:59,042 --> 00:11:00,958
I've been here ten years.

200
00:11:01,061 --> 00:11:03,928
I was interim chief of neuro
before Shepherd in his red cape

201
00:11:04,030 --> 00:11:05,646
swooped in from New York.

202
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:10,368
- Mark Sloan, plastics.
- We've met. Three times.

203
00:11:14,191 --> 00:11:18,426
I don't know why Mr. Bimm
ever let her join band.

204
00:11:18,528 --> 00:11:21,595
- Not like she's
a master flautist...
- OK, get out!

205
00:11:21,697 --> 00:11:23,978
Mr. Bimm said
to stay until her...

206
00:11:24,033 --> 00:11:26,217
I got it! I'm
seizure patrol now.

207
00:11:30,139 --> 00:11:33,107
- Your friends are asses.
- They're not my friends.

208
00:11:33,209 --> 00:11:36,211
Once you spazz out in school,
friends are hard to come by.

209
00:11:36,313 --> 00:11:40,164
You can't help the epilepsy, but
nobody made you join the marching band.

210
00:11:40,266 --> 00:11:42,967
- It's spreading nerd on nerd.
- I like being in the band.

211
00:11:43,069 --> 00:11:46,432
It's the one thing I'm good at.
What'd you do in high school?

212
00:11:46,456 --> 00:11:48,689
- I wrestled.
- You're a wrestler?

213
00:11:48,791 --> 00:11:51,509
- You wearing tights under that?
- It was a long time ago.

214
00:11:51,611 --> 00:11:53,394
That was high school,
I'm a surgeon now.

215
00:11:53,496 --> 00:11:57,231
How would you feel if you seized every
time you went into the operating room?

216
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:59,434
Yeah, OK.

217
00:12:02,521 --> 00:12:06,490
You realize, as your doctor,
I'm not recommending this, right?

218
00:12:06,592 --> 00:12:08,726
I need to get through
my surgeries today.

219
00:12:08,828 --> 00:12:11,591
You're gonna get through
them, just hurt later.

220
00:12:11,615 --> 00:12:14,581
You heard of a
Dr. Nelson in neuro?

221
00:12:16,019 --> 00:12:19,287
Oh, yeah. Shadow Shepherd.

222
00:12:19,388 --> 00:12:21,222
- Shadow Shepherd?
- Yeah.

223
00:12:21,324 --> 00:12:22,707
He's a solid surgeon,

224
00:12:22,809 --> 00:12:25,509
but sort of the JV player
to Shepherd's varsity.

225
00:12:25,612 --> 00:12:29,497
The B team to Shepherd's A. The
bricklayer to Shepherd's architect.

